</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="68" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="68">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Augener" authorityYear="1918" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Lepidonotus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lepidonotus hupferi" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hupferi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Lepidonotus hupferi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents a wide distribution. Futher studies are required to enable us to understand if it is a cryptogenic species, because there are no studies to show that it is a species complex, and its origin was not determined
</paragraph>
